    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nonmetallic chemical element (O). It is a colorless, odorless, tasteless gas, the most plentiful element in the Earth's crust; its most important compound is water.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
